[src:eigenvalue-solvers/eigenvalue-algorithm] Iterative algorithms solve the eigenvalue problem by producing sequences that converge to the eigenvalues.
[src:eigenvalue-solvers/eigenvalue-algorithm] Some algorithms also produce sequences of vectors that converge to the eigenvectors.
[src:eigenvalue-solvers/eigenvalue-algorithm] Most commonly, the eigenvalue sequences are expressed as sequences of similar matrices which converge to a triangular or diagonal form, allowing the eigenvalues to be read easily.
[src:eigenvalue-solvers/eigenvalue-algorithm] The eigenvector sequences are expressed as the corresponding similarity matrices.
